This paper deals with fairness in machine learning algorithms, specifically in the context of online decision making. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses discrimination and bias, which could potentially fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
